>>b4f7364d-80ca-44f8-8fe3-9593340f73ff
>Just like the Patriot got challenged on 4A grounds, right?
While the PA could have been applied to anyone, it wasn't. Most people weren't impacted by it at all. That's why it was never challenged. There's way too damn many people using crypto, VPNs, and filesharing for them to tolerate legislation of this sort.
